Minister Gopal Bhargava handed out 10,000 wooden bats to newlyweds and their family members at a mass wedding ceremony over the weekend. JOHANNESBURG - A minister in India has come up with a controversial way to reduce domestic violence caused by alcohol abuse.Minister Gopal Bhargava handed out 10,000 wooden bats to newlyweds and their family members at a mass wedding ceremony over the weekend. Some 700 couples tied the knot during the marathon session.The bats are meant to be used in self-defence by new brides seeking respite from abusive spouses.Alcohol is not banned in the province but the Indian government is increasingly regulating liquor consumption countrywide.